refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;

 public Vtiful\Kernel\ExcelVtiful\Kernel\Excel::computeFormula
 boolenable&true;

Enables or disables compute-on-write. When enabled, subsequent calls to Vtiful\Kernel\Excel::insertFormula evaluate the formula against the cells written so far and store the computed value as the cached result, so the saved file shows correct values before the spreadsheet application recalculates. It is off by default, in which case formulas keep a zero cached result. It works best in normal mode; in constant-memory mode, references to already flushed cells resolve as blank.

&reftitle.parameters;


  enable

   Whether to enable compute-on-write for subsequent formula insertions.
